<div id="stitle" style="display:none;">Notebook Entry</div>
<dl id="n41034d"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n41" href="#n41034d">N41 (VI.B.33)</a>:  <a href="../../FF/fnbs/n41all.htm#n41034d"> 34(d)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> uninscribed / slab Emmett</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources"><font color="green">[&hellip;]</font> And then we came to the grave of Robert <mark>Emmet</mark>, &ldquo;the saddest spot in Ireland,&rdquo; was the remark of Gladstone when the <mark>uninscribed slab</mark> was pointed out to him. He was informed in reply to a query on the subject that Dr. Madden&apos;s authority, supported by that of a nephew of Emmet&apos;s, left no uncertainty as to that spot being the actual burial place of the patriot. <small> J.B. Hall, <a name="HRRR" href="../../FF/fdra/fdex.htm#HRRR"><cite title="source">Random Records of a Reporter</cite></a> (n.d.) &lsquo;Visit to Hawarden.&rsquo; 223</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
